metadata.name: CPU Die Shots #48
metadata.description:
Two color palettes (2 Bits and Acetone) and a unique CPU die shot is generated based on unique hash seeds.

The definition of a die (wikipedia):
A die, in the context of integrated circuits, is a small block of semiconducting material on which a given functional circuit is fabricated. Typically, integrated circuits are produced in large batches on a single wafer of electronic-grade silicon (EGS) or other semiconductor (such as GaAs) through processes such as photolithography. The wafer is cut (diced) into many pieces, each containing one copy of the circuit. Each of these pieces is called a die.

Specials
- press "c" to recreate a new Landscape
- press "g" to activate the "Gallery Mode", piece change each 60s

Generative Art created by Michael Vogt (@neophob).

metadata.name: griiids #49
metadata.description:
A minimal algorithm that generates a grid of rectangles. There can be between 7 and 39 columns in increments of 4. There are 10 available colour palettes.

The algorithm moves through each column and generates a series of rectangles with random heights and gaps (also of random heights) between each rectangle. Each new rectangle will also select a random colour from the selected palette.

metadata.name: Perspective 1.0 #5
metadata.description: While studying civil engineering I always loved mechanical drawing classes. The way that perspective brings anything into context is magnificent. A simple cube could appear floating if it's above the horizon line, as a box standing near your feet if it's below the horizon, or as a building in front of you if it's drawn just over the horizon line. This project explores different ways to draw a box using a 2-point perspective and 4 color schemes. Find your perfect cube and let it be the rarest Red-one.

metadata.name: Bézier Bloom #5
metadata.description:
When spring doesn't come soon enough, we can make our own spring. Branch by branch, petal by petal, watch a tree come into being and bloom.

Controls:
"a": toggle between animation and final drawing.
"i": toggle day/night (invert colors).
"p": pause/resume animation.
"s": save image.
A tree grows different during the day and at night. You can become a master of time to nurture your own unique tree.

These interactive drawings are made entirely of Bézier curves.
Created by Elsif (ElsifThen@twitter) using p5js.

metadata.name: Alma de Flor #7
metadata.description:
Alma de Flor is a project inspired by nature and floral afterlife. 

Plants are alive, they grow on our planet and populate almost every continent on earth. 
They live, grow and die. 
Some plants live a long time, some others don't. Kind of like humans, they change and evolve. They have souls, but they're different from ours, they differ in energy. 

Living in a tropical country allowed me to live in a place with huge biodiversity, so for me, this is how a born European, raised Latino person connects with this feeling.
